# entropiaorme dev-environment reverse proxy.
#
# Fronts the local `just dev` stack on a stable `entropiaorme.localhost`
# hostname so URLs in the browser, DevTools, Postman, screenshots, and
# similar tooling read as a hostname rather than a port number.
#
# Start with `just proxy-up`; `just proxy-status` for a liveness check;
# `just proxy-down` to stop. Skipping the Caddy install keeps the
# existing port-based `just dev` flow unmodified.
#
# HTTPS is served via Caddy's local CA (`tls internal`). One-time
# elevated step `caddy trust` installs Caddy's root certificate into
# the OS trust store so the dev hostnames load without warnings in
# browsers, Tauri's WebView2, and other native HTTPS clients.

entropiaorme.localhost {
	tls internal
	reverse_proxy localhost:5173
}

# Additional checkouts of this repo (sharing this dev machine but bound
# to distinct frontend ports) drop their own routing stanzas into the
# directory below. Fragments use the same `tls internal` shape so each
# checkout gets its own auto-provisioned cert. The glob matches zero
# files in a fresh clone, which Caddy accepts as a no-op rather than
# an error; the fragment is generated when the additional checkout
# comes online and a `caddy reload` picks it up.
#
# Fragments belong in the *main worktree's* `.dev/Caddyfile.worktrees/`
# (Caddy resolves this `import` relative to the loaded file's
# directory). `scripts/caddy-lifecycle.ps1` (invoked by
# `scripts/dev-launch.ps1`'s defensive reload and by the `just proxy-*`
# recipes) always loads this Caddyfile from the main worktree
# (resolved via `git worktree list --porcelain`), so every active
# checkout's fragment survives any reload regardless of which checkout
# triggered it.
import .dev/Caddyfile.worktrees/*.caddy
